<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Commercial gas range service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Gas ranges are the workhorse of LA commercial kitchens. Predictable failure modes, accessible parts.</h2>

    <p>Commercial gas ranges are the dominant cooking equipment in LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside restaurant kitchens. 4 to 10 burner configurations standard. Each burner produces 25,000 to 35,000 BTU (vs 12,000 to 18,000 BTU residential), supporting continuous high-heat cooking through 12 to 16 hour service days.</p>

    <p>The dominant brands: <strong>Vulcan VR Series</strong> (VR-24, VR-36, VR-48, VR-60, VR-72, ITW Food Equipment Group), <strong>Garland Master Series M</strong> (Welbilt), <strong>Wolf Challenger XL</strong> (Wolf Industrial / Sub-Zero Group commercial division, distinct from residential Wolf), <strong>American Range Performer ARTGS</strong> (Cypress, CA local manufacturer), <strong>Southbend</strong> (Middleby), <strong>Imperial</strong> (Imperial Manufacturing), <strong>Montague</strong> (Welbilt). All seven are repairable through year 15+ with proper maintenance.</p>

    <p>The failure modes are predictable. Igniter failure at year 4 to 7. Thermocouple wear at year 5 to 8. Burner head clog from carbon and grease accumulation. LA gas line pressure issues (commercial requires 1\" line minimum, often undersized in older buildings). None of these are catastrophic. All are repairable with parts on the truck.</p>

    <p><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410).  scope. BBB A+ accredited.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 COMMON FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Common gas range failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we diagnose most often.</h2>

    <ol class="failure-list">
      <li><strong>Igniter failure (per burner, year 4 to 7).</strong> Spark electrode pits from carbon and grease buildup, intermittent spark eventually fails. $260 to $440 per burner.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermocouple wear (gas safety, year 5 to 8).</strong> Thermocouple millivolts drop below 14 mV, gas valve won't stay open. $220 to $340 per replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner head clog.</strong> Heavy carbon and grease accumulation in burner ports affects flame quality and BTU output. $180 to $290 per burner cleaning.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot light extinguishing (older models).</strong> Pre-electronic-ignition ranges with standing pilots. Pilot orifice clogged or thermocouple weak. $220 to $380.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve degradation (year 8+).</strong> Main gas control valve wear creates pressure inconsistencies across burners. $580 to $980 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Oven thermostat drift (separate component below burners).</strong> Oven below the range top runs hot or cold relative to setpoint. $260 to $420 replacement plus calibration.</li>
      <li><strong>LA gas line pressure issues.</strong> Commercial range requires 1\" gas line minimum from meter. Older buildings sometimes have 3/4\" line that worked for previous lighter equipment, now starves the range. We diagnose with manometer; line resizing is plumber trade, we coordinate.</li>
      <li><strong>Door hinge wear (range oven door).</strong> Heavy door drops over time. $260 to $440 hinge replacement.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent gas range repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four gas range jobs from the past 90 days. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Restaurant in West Hollywood · Vulcan VR-36, 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Two burners not igniting reliably plus thermocouple weak on the rear-left burner. Diagnosed: two igniters with pitted electrodes plus thermocouple millivolts at 11 mV (needs 14+). Replaced two igniters and the thermocouple. Tested all four burners full ignition cycle. Total: $120 + $360 igniters + $200 thermocouple = $560.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Mexican restaurant in East LA · Garland M48-2G with griddle, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Three burners ignition issues plus uneven flame on remaining burner. Diagnosed: three igniters worn plus main gas valve degradation creating pressure inconsistency across all burners. Replaced three igniters and main gas valve. Tested all burners and griddle. Total: $120 + $540 igniters + $620 valve + $80 supplies = $980.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Catering kitchen in Pasadena · Wolf Challenger XL CHSC60 6-burner, 5 years old</h3>
        <p>Oven below range running 35°F low at 350°F setpoint, plus one burner igniter failing. Diagnosed: oven thermostat drift plus single-burner igniter end-of-life. Replaced oven thermostat with calibration plus burner igniter. Total: $120 + $260 igniter + $260 thermostat = $640. Wolf Industrial parts ordered through commercial authorized network.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Korean BBQ restaurant in Koreatown · American Range ARTGS-244, 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Multi-burner cleaning (heavy carbon buildup from continuous high-volume Korean BBQ operation) plus two thermocouples weak. Replaced both thermocouples, deep-cleaned all four burners. Total: $120 + $400 thermocouples + $200 burner cleaning = $720. Set restaurant on quarterly maintenance contract going forward.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service, what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> all major commercial gas range brands (Vulcan VR Series, Garland Master Series M, Wolf Challenger XL, American Range Performer ARTGS, Southbend, Imperial, Montague). 4 to 10 burner configurations. Standard ranges, ranges with griddle/charbroiler modules, ranges with salamander broilers (see <a href="/commercial/range-repair/restaurant-range-salamander-repair/">salamander repair page</a>). French top configurations (see <a href="/commercial/range-repair/french-top-range-repair/">French top page</a>). Igniters, thermocouples, gas valves, burner head cleaning, oven thermostat service, door hinges.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>New range installation (specialty installer trade with gas line and ventilation work)</li>
      <li>Gas line resizing or new gas plumbing (plumber trade with city permits)</li>
      <li>Type I exhaust hood work (see <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">exhaust hood repair</a>)</li>
      <li>Wood-fired or charcoal ranges (specialty trade)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

